  "texts": [
    "Recent studies (Hu et al., 2023; Ruis et al., 2023) highlight language models' struggle with humor, irony, and conversational maxims.",
    "Previous evaluations either focused on singular phenomena or had limited sample sizes, like (Deng et al., 2014; Sileo et al., 2022; Qi et al., 2023).",
    "To the best of our knowledge, we are the first ones to combine major aspects of pragmatics to create a quantifiable benchmark.",
    "With the help of language experts, we selected existing datasets covering important pragmatic aspects.",
    "Specifically, we select Circa (Louis et al., 2020), GRICE (Zheng et al., 2021), FigQA (Liu et al., 2022), FLUTE (Chakrabarty et al., 2022), IMPPRES (Jeretic et al., 2020), and NOPE (Parrish et al., 2021)."
  ],
